Subject: Re: [T2] Release Shaft Main Bushing?

On Wed, 9 Oct 2002, Andrew Mueller wrote:

> Got 2 release shaft bushing replacements.
...
> The plastic ones seemed to move pretty
> easily so you can line up the holes with the
> allignment screw, but the new copper bushing now in
> there will not budge to line up with the allignment
> screw.  Any ideas on how to make this thing move
> around?  thanks

_Don't_ bang around on it with a punch or hammer!  You'll mushroom the
ends making the problem worse.

Use a wooden or plastic drift to move it around with hammer taps.  You
might also get hold of it with a small set of water pump pliars
(channelocks).

George
